cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.CV 

The paper discusses multimedia mining, which involves the extraction of implicit knowledge, multimedia data relationships, or other patterns not explicitly stored in multimedia files. This topic falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the retrieval, indexing, and classification of multimedia data, which involves efficient information fusion of different modalities, making it relevant to the categories of deep learning (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), and computer vision (cs.CV).
